declarations.comments: de-variant an effect stack containing only the halogen effect, so that it can be used for query/action evaluation
declarations.title: runHalogen

declarations.comments: Convert State effects to use the state of the halogen component.
declarations.title: runStateHalogen

declarations.comments: Lifts the "effect" effect into HalogenF, so that you can use runHalogen
declarations.title: runEffectHalogen

declarations.comments: Lifts the "aff" effect into HalogenF, so that you can use runHalogen
declarations.title: runAffHalogen

declarations.comments: The query function from Halogen.Query.HalogenM without the Free wrapper, so it can be put into a variant.
declarations.title: query

declarations.comments: For certain effects in the Run effect stack it can be useful to evaluate it using a component with the effect algebra as its query algebra, and using the effect id as the component slot id (with Unit as the index). runChildHalogen automates that.
declarations.title: runChildHalogen
